  "text": "Recall that according to theorem 1.1 of [CITATION_1] , theorem 2.5 can be extended to the colored case when we work over a field of characteristic zero. Let P be a differential graded colored prop over a field of characteristic zero. The homotopy theory of homotopy P -algebras does not depend, up to Dwyer-Kan equivalence, on the choice of a cofibrant resolution of P . This result works also for 1-colored dg props (i.e. the props of definition 2.3) over a field of any characteristic when we consider props with non-empty inputs.",
